}
```

Dark mode: invert around `primary-950` (`#001038`) as background, keep `--primary` at a lighter step (use primary-400 `#5379FF` for sufficient contrast) — define `.dark` overrides when dark mode is scheduled.

## Typography & spacing

- Font: Inter (variable), system-ui fallback. Tabular numerals (`font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums`) for points values and tables.
- Type scale: page title `text-2xl font-semibold`, section `text-lg font-semibold`, body `text-sm`, captions `text-xs text-muted-foreground`. Don't invent intermediate sizes.
- Spacing on the 4px grid; standard page padding `p-6` (admin), `p-4` (portal mobile). Card gaps `gap-4` or `gap-6`.
- Points values are first-class content: display with thousands separators, gold color for emphasis contexts, and never truncated.

## Layout

- Admin: shadcn `Sidebar` navigation + topbar; content max-width `max-w-7xl`; usable from 1024px and up.
- Portal: mobile-first (design at 360px, enhance upward); single-column flows; bottom-reachable primary actions on mobile.
- Tables on mobile collapse to stacked cards — never horizontal scroll for primary content.

## Interaction & state patterns

- **Every async view has 4 designed states:** loading (skeletons matching final layout — no spinners-as-pages), empty (explain + primary action), error (human message + retry), success.
- **Forms:** React Hook Form + Zod. Validate on blur, re-validate on change after first error. Errors inline under fields; never only in a toast. Submit buttons show inline loading and disable; never disable submit pre-emptively for untouched forms.
- **Destructive or irreversible actions** (revoke points, delete rule, cancel redemption): `ConfirmDialog` restating the concrete effect ("Remove 500 points from Jane — new balance 750"); destructive button styled `variant="destructive"`. High-risk deletes require typed confirmation.
- **Feedback:** `toast` (sonner) for results of background actions; success toasts are brief, error toasts persist until dismissed and say what to do next. Never use `alert()`/`confirm()`.
- **Optimistic updates** for toggles and adjustments via TanStack Query, with rollback + error toast on failure.
- **Dialogs vs Sheets vs pages:** quick confirmation/single-field → `Dialog`; inspect-heavy side content (payloads, details) → `Sheet`; anything with > ~6 fields or multi-step → dedicated page.
- Loyalty celebration moments (tier-up, redemption success) may use animation, but must be dismissible and respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## Accessibility (non-negotiable)

- WCAG 2.1 AA. Text contrast ≥ 4.5:1 — note: gold `#FFB200` on white fails for text; use `gold-600 #D99700` for text, reserve 500 for icons/large numerals ≥ 24px.
- Full keyboard operability; visible focus rings (`--ring` navy) never removed.
- Every input labelled (no placeholder-as-label); icons-only buttons get `aria-label`; meaning never conveyed by color alone (pair badges with text).
- Announce async result states to screen readers (toast lib handles this; verify).

## Copy & tone

- Plain, encouraging language in the portal ("You earned 120 points"); precise, factual language in admin ("+120 earn · order #1042").
- Sentence case everywhere (buttons, titles, labels). No exclamation marks in admin; sparing use in portal celebrations.
- Numbers, dates, currency formatted via shared utils (locale-aware) — never inline `toFixed`/string concat.
